@page "/terms"
@inject SiteConfig Site

<PageTitle>Terms of Service — @Site.SiteTitle</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Terms of service for @Site.SiteTitle" />
</HeadContent>

<section class="section page-head">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Terms of Service</p>
        <h1>The house rules</h1>
        <p class="muted">Plain language, no gotchas. This page describes the terms for using this site.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="legal">
    <div class="container prose">
        <h2>Accepting these terms</h2>
        <p>
            By browsing this site, signing in, or posting a comment, you agree to these terms.
            If you don't agree with something here, the remedy is simple: don't use the site.
        </p>

        <h2>Your account</h2>
        <p>
            Signing in happens through a third-party provider (such as GitHub, Google, or Discord) —
            this site never sees or stores a password. You're responsible for the security of the
            provider account you sign in with. You can stop using the site at any time, and you can
            ask for your account and content to be deleted (see the contact section below).
        </p>

        <h2>Comments and content you post</h2>
        <p>
            Comments should stay civil. Content that is illegal, harassing, hateful, spammy, or
            malicious (including attempts to inject code) may be hidden or deleted, and repeat
            offenders may have their accounts removed — at the site owner's sole discretion,
            with or without notice.
        </p>
        <p>
            You keep ownership of what you write. By posting, you give this site permission to
            display your comment alongside your chosen display name or anonymously if you selected
            that option. You can delete your own comments at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>No warranty</h2>
        <p>
            This site is a personal project, provided "as is" without warranties of any kind.
            It may go down, change, or be discontinued at any time. The site owner is not liable
            for any damages arising from its use, to the maximum extent permitted by law.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
            These terms may change as the site evolves. The version published on this page is
            always the current one.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            Questions about these terms go to
            <a href="mailto:@Site.ContactEmail">@Site.ContactEmail</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="muted">
            This page is written in good faith by @Site.OwnerName and is not legal advice.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
